from sklearn.tree import DecisionTreeRegressor
from sklearn.model_selection import train_test_split
from collections import OrderedDict

scores = {}

for feature in data:
    # TODODataFrame'drop'
    new_data = data.copy()
    new_data.drop([feature], axis = 1, inplace=True)

    new_y = data[feature]

    # TODO
    X_train, X_test, y_train, y_test = train_test_split(new_data, new_y, test_size=0.25, random_state=42)

    # TODODecisionTreeRegressor
    regressor = DecisionTreeRegressor(random_state=42).fit(X_train, y_train)

    # TODO
    score = regressor.predict(X_test)

    scores[feature] = regressor.score(X_test, y_test)
    
scores = pd.Series(scores).sort_values()

In [18]:



    


outliers = []
turkey_count = np.zeros(data.shape[0]) # mask
for feature in log_data:
    # TODOQ125th
    Q1 = np.percentile(log_data[feature], 25)
    
    # TODOQ375th
    Q3 = np.percentile(log_data[feature], 75)
    
    step = (Q3-Q1) * 1.5
    
    turkey = ~((log_data[feature] >= Q1 - step ) & (log_data[feature] <= Q3 + step)) # tukey
    turkey_count += turkey.astype(int)
    
#  outliers
outliers = np.where(turkey_count > 1)[0]

print outliers

from sklearn.mixture import GaussianMixture
from sklearn.metrics import silhouette_score
from sklearn.cluster import KMeans

clusterer_arr = pd.DataFrame()

for index in range(2, 50):
    clusterer_estimator = {}
    
    # TODO
    clusterer = KMeans(n_clusters=index, random_state=42, n_jobs=-1).fit(reduced_data)
    clusterer_estimator['clusterer'] = clusterer

    # TODO
    preds = clusterer.predict(reduced_data)
    clusterer_estimator['preds'] = preds

    # TODO
    centers = clusterer.cluster_centers_
    clusterer_estimator['centers'] = centers

    # TODO
    sample_preds = clusterer.predict(pca_samples)
    clusterer_estimator['sample_preds'] = sample_preds

    # TODOmean silhouette coefficient
    score = silhouette_score(reduced_data, clusterer.labels_)
    clusterer_estimator['score'] = score
    
    clusterer_arr = clusterer_arr.append(clusterer_estimator, ignore_index=True)
    
print 'Train End!'

from sklearn.ensemble import RandomForestClassifier
from sklearn.model_selection import train_test_split

# 
cluster_data = pd.read_csv("cluster.csv")
y = cluster_data['Region']
X = cluster_data.drop(['Region'], axis = 1)

# 
X_train, X_test, y_train, y_test = train_test_split(X, y, test_size=0.2, random_state=24)

clf = RandomForestClassifier(random_state=24)
clf.fit(X_train, y_train)
print "cluster", clf.score(X_test, y_test)

# cluster
X_train = X_train.copy()
X_train.drop(['cluster'], axis=1, inplace=True)
X_test = X_test.copy()
X_test.drop(['cluster'], axis=1, inplace=True)
clf.fit(X_train, y_train)
print "cluster", clf.score(X_test, y_test)
